Here's an implementation of a function to allow users to comment using Java:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Comment Function</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            min-height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }

        .comment-container {
            background-color: white;
            padding: 2rem;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            width: 400px;
        }

        #commentText {
            width: 100%;
            height: 200px;
            padding: 1rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 4px;
            resize: vertical;
        }

        .author-section {
            margin-top: 2rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Basic HTML structure -->
    <h1>Leave a Comment</h1>

    <!-- Button to start commenting -->
    <button onclick="createCommentForm()" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
        Start Commenting
    </button>

    <!-- Comment area -->
    <div class="comment-container">
        <textarea id="commentText" placeholder="Write your comment here..."></textarea>
    </div>

    <!-- List of users (would be populated elsewhere) -->
    <h3>Comments by Users:</h3>
    <div id="userComments"></div>

    <!-- JavaScript code -->
    <script>
        function createCommentForm() {
            // Create a user object with name and email
            const userInfo = {
                name: 'Anonymous User',
                email: 'anonymous@example.com'
            };

            // Get the current time
            const currentTime = new Date().getTime();

            // Add to users array as an anonymous comment by default
            userInfo.userComments.push(`Commented at ${currentTime}${'\n'}${userInfo.email}`);

            // Clear the textarea
            document.getElementById('commentText').value = '';
        }

        function styleCommentArea() {
            const commentContainer = document.querySelector('.comment-container');
            const userCommentsDiv = document.getElementById('userComments');

            // List of users would go here ( populated elsewhere)
            // For now, set placeholder if no users
            if (!userInfo) {
                commentContainer.innerHTML += '<textarea id="commentText" style="border: 1px solid red; height: 200px;">Write your comment here...</textarea>';
            }

            userCommentsDiv.innerHTML = userInfo.userComments.join('<br>');
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This code provides a simple comment system with the following features:

1. A "Start Commenting" button that triggers the creation of a text input area
2. An anonymous default user who comments first (can be replaced with real authentication)
3. Timestamps for each comment
4. A section showing which users have made comments

To use this function, you would need to:

1. Replace `styleCommentArea()` with your actual CSS styles
2. Populate the `userInfo` object with real user data when the application is actually used (e.g., via a login system)
3. Add more functionality based on authentication and permissions

The code uses basic HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create a functional commenting area that can be extended with additional features like:

- User authentication
- Different comment permissions for different users
- Email notifications when comments are made
- Loading indicators while comments are being processed
- spam prevention measures
